                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.B.14.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article 72</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian"
                        notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00"
                        >undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>Redraft U.K. proposal to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Any disputes which may arise in connection with Articles 65 and 63 and
                            Annexes 6, 7 and 8 of the present Treaty shall be referred to a
                            Conciliation Commission composed of an equal number of representatives
                            of the United Nations Government concerned and of the Italian
                            Government. If agreement has not been reached within three months of the
                            dispute having been referred to the Conciliation Commission, the “<hi
                                rend="italic">dispute shall be referred to the Treaty Executive
                                Council constituted by Article 75</hi>” (<hi rend="italic">see
                                Australian amendment to Article 75</hi>) and if not resolved by that
                            Council within a period of two months, the dispute shall at the request
                            of any party to the dispute be referred to the International Court of
                            Justice.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Similar provisions for Treaties for: <list>
                        <item>—Roumania;</item>
                        <item>—Bulgaria;</item>
                        <item>—Hungary;</item>
                        <item>—Finland.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
